🔵 Q7. Total Revenue per Product per Region (MULTI-JOIN)
🧱 Table Schema

orders

order_id	customer_id	product_id	amount
1	101	10	500
2	102	20	300
3	101	20	200

customers

customer_id	customer_name	region_id
101	Alice	1
102	Bob	2

regions

region_id	region_name
1	East
2	West

products

product_id	product_name
10	iPhone
20	iPad
🎯 Question

Find total revenue by region and product.

✅ Query
SELECT
    r.region_name,
    p.product_name,
    SUM(o.amount) AS total_revenue
FROM orders o
JOIN customers c ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id
JOIN regions r ON c.region_id = r.region_id
JOIN products p ON o.product_id = p.product_id
GROUP BY r.region_name, p.product_name;

🔵 Q8. Customers Who Bought Products from Multiple Categories
🧱 Table Schema

orders

order_id	customer_id	product_id
1	101	10
2	101	11
3	102	10

products

product_id	product_name	category
10	iPhone	Electronics
11	Sofa	Furniture
🎯 Question

Find customers who have purchased from more than one category.

✅ Query
SELECT
    o.customer_id
FROM orders o
JOIN products p ON o.product_id = p.product_id
GROUP BY o.customer_id
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT p.category) > 1;

🔵 Q9. Most Popular Product per Region (Apple Favorite)
🧱 Table Schema

Same as Q7.

🎯 Question

Find the top-selling product (by revenue) in each region.

✅ Query
WITH region_sales AS (
    SELECT
        r.region_name,
        p.product_name,
        SUM(o.amount) AS total_revenue
    FROM orders o
    JOIN customers c ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id
    JOIN regions r ON c.region_id = r.region_id
    JOIN products p ON o.product_id = p.product_id
    GROUP BY r.region_name, p.product_name
)
SELECT region_name, product_name, total_revenue
FROM (
    SELECT *,
           RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY region_name ORDER BY total_revenue DESC) AS rnk
    FROM region_sales
) ranked
WHERE rnk = 1;

🔵 Q10. Average Order Value per Customer (Nested Joins + Aggregation)
🧱 Table Schema

Same as Q7.

🎯 Question

Find each customer’s average order value (AOV).

✅ Query
SELECT
    c.customer_name,
    AVG(o.amount) AS avg_order_value
FROM customers c
JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
GROUP BY c.customer_name;

